A Cuban oasis lurking unsuspecting amid the Dominican Chiefdoms of Washington Heights. They make ropa vieja only on Fridays. The bacalao is also not there every day. You can sit at the main bar and order your plate to be assembled whichever way you want (foods are ready behind the counter but it is not self-service), or ask for a la carte dishes. At the back they have a separate "real" bar area with slightly dimmer lights and slightly louder music if your wish is to focus on sipping rather than chewing. Food was great, not salty, not bland, not boring, portion sizes were big without being indecent like at other places, and prices were pretty ok. Oh and of course they have legit cubano sandwiches. The fact that Floridita is open 24/7 makes it sound like this place is a grub hole, but it is not. This is a nice, clean, good vibes restaurant to sit down and enjoy a hearty meal. I could bring any friend of mine to eat there. My mom would probably want something a bit more expensive, a bit less busy.
